  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7134 sitting between the max positive gamma at 7100 and the strong 7150 GEX wall, dealers are in active selling mode to hedge their long gamma positions as spot pushes higher. The PIN regime and massive positive gamma concentration from 7100-7200 creates a strong magnet effect, with dealers providing natural resistance on any further upside momentum through systematic selling. Watch 7100 as the key pivot - any dip back below should trigger dealer buying to re-hedge, while a sustained break above 7150 faces the next major resistance wall at 7175-7200.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 7100 with limited upside past 7150.",
